canonical:
  title: 君子寺
  author: 兪好仁
  language: lzh
  text: 烟樹平沉雨意遲晩來看竹坐移時老禪碧眼渾如舊更檢前年此日詩
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 君子寺
  author: 兪好仁
  language: lzh
  text: 烟樹平沉雨意遲。晩來看竹坐移時。老禪碧眼渾如舊。更檢前年此日詩。
korean:
  title: 군자사
  author: 유호인
  language: kor
  text: |-
    내 낀 숲은 어두울 제 비 내릴 뜻이 더디어라
    늦게 와서 대를 보려 오랫동안 앉았었소
    늙은 선사 푸른 눈이 예와 다름 없어
    지난 해 읊은 시를 다시금 읽어보네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0040&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Gunja Temple
  author: Yu Ho-in
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Mist settles on the trees as rain delays its coming.
    Late in the day, I sit long among the bamboo.
    The old master's jade eyes remain unchanged,
    As I read again the verses from this day last year.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Gunja Temple (君子寺) is a Buddhist temple, with 'gunja' literally meaning 'gentleman' or 'superior person,' suggesting a place of cultivation and refinement.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'jade eyes' (碧眼) refer to the piercing spiritual insight traditionally associated with Buddhist masters, here implying the continuity of enlightened perception across time.
